<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 00:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Ministers Return To Posts  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PANAMA CITY (AP) -- Five days after Panamanian President Mireya
Moscoso's Cabinet resigned, nearly all 13 ministers returned to
their posts Monday following the reassignment of the economic
minister.
</P>
<P>
   The mass resignation Aug. 16 came amid criticism that the
government wasn't doing enough to solve the country's economic
problems.
</P>
<P>
   The ministers returned to their posts after Moscoso announced
the Economic Minister Victor Juliao would be made the public works
minister.
</P>
<P>
   The country's vice minister of finance was named the new
economic minister.
</P>
<P>
   Since Moscoso became president last September, residents have
complained that her government has not done enough to fight poverty
and reduce widespread unemployment. Moscoso has said she was
satisfied with her government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
