<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 00:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Martha's Vineyard Airport Closed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST TISBURY, Mass. (AP) -- Authorities shut down Martha's
Vineyard Airport Monday night after discovering a suspicious piece
of abandoned luggage.
</P>
<P>
   A state police bomb squad was called to the scene shortly after
the luggage was discovered at about 6 p.m. Officers took an initial
X-ray, but ''something didn't appear right,'' state police Sgt. Tim
White said.
</P>
<P>
   The airport, on the island off of the Massachusetts coast, was
closed and evacuated.
</P>
<P>
   Police requested more sophisticated equipment to examine the
luggage and were waiting for it to arrive from the mainland late
Monday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
