<HEADLINE> TWA Flight 800 Crash Still Mystery  </HEADLINE>
By RANDOLPH E. SCHMID
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Four years after an explosion destroyed TWA
Flight 800 and killed all 230 aboard, federal investigators are
taking what they hope will be a final look into the mystery of what
happened.
</P>
<P>
   The National Transportation Safety Board opens a two-day meeting
Tuesday to review the evidence collected in its investigation.
</P>
<P>
   Speculation has ranged from a spark caused by electrical wiring,
