<HEADLINE> A 46-year-old man is jailed for having sex with 13-year-old girl  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - A judge sent a 46-year-old man to jail
for having sex with a 13-year-old girl and claiming that he didn't
know her age.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't care how old the girl was; if you're climbing through
a bedroom window to see her, you know you're doing something
wrong,'' state Supreme Court Justice David D. Egan said Monday.
''The baloney about you being seduced by her is nothing more than
garbage.''
</P>
<P>
   Joseph Auld of West Seneca, Erie County, will serve two to six
years. He pleaded guilty to second-degree rape for having sex with
the girl in February.
</P>
<P>
   After meeting the girl, Auld mailed her phone cards so she could
call him without ringing up long-distance tolls, then arranged to
climb through her window at night, said Monroe County Assistant
District Attorney Mary Beth Feindt.
</P>
<P>
   The girl willingly had sex with Auld but state law deemed her
incapable of consent because of her age.
</P>
<P>
   The girl, who was living with a friend because her mother was
seriously ill, now resides with her father in another state.
</P>
<P>
   Although Auld told Greece police that he thought the girl was
19, police seized handwritten notes from his home showing that the
girl gave him her date of birth.
</P>
