<HEADLINE> Baby Panda's Birthday Celebrated  </HEADLINE>
By KIMBERLY LAMKE
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- They lined up early and stayed late. Hua
Mei-niacs were out in force to celebrate the history-making baby
giant panda's first birthday.
</P>
<P>
   Hundreds of zoo-goers lined up before the park's 7:30 a.m.
opening Monday, hoping to be among the first to wish the 60-pound
bundle of black-and-white joy a happy birthday.
</P>
<P>
   ''We've been watching her on the Internet, and we've visited so
many times, she feels a little like a part of the family now,''
said Jim Helniak, who showed up with his wife, Sue, and their
10-year-old daughter, Kelley.
</P>
<P>
   As the first surviving Ailuropoda melanoleuca born in the United
States, Hua Mei has attracted the attention of admirers and
scientists alike.
</P>
<P>
   June Baker, 79, and her 39-year-old daughter Joanna, arrived at
the zoo at 8 a.m., and quickly made their way to the panda
enclosure.
</P>
<P>
   ''We've seen the panda before, but we wanted to come today and
experience all the festivities,'' Joanna Baker said. ''I wish she
knew just how much everyone wants to celebrate her birthday.''
</P>
<P>
   Early in the morning, keepers presented Hua Mei with a special
cake made of bamboo frozen in ice and a group of children from
Mexico sang a Spanish birthday song.
</P>
<P>
   ''She interacted with her birthday cake,'' said Kathy Hawk, the
zoo's senior giant panda keeper, ''even throwing it on the ground a
few times, just like a typical child.''
</P>
<P>
   Also included in the festivities were the signing of a giant
birthday card, a bell tower chiming the ''Happy Birthday'' tune at
the panda's time of birth and a $2 million donation by Pacific Bell
to support panda research at the zoo over the next four years.
</P>
<P>
   All three of the San Diego Zoo's pandas -- Hua Mei, and her
parents, Bai Yun, 9, and Shi Shi, 21 -- are on loan from China. The
contract expires in 2004 but the zoo is hoping for an extension.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: www.sandiegozoo.org
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
