<HEADLINE> Dolphins WR Thomas Injures Hip  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Miami Dolphins wide receiver Lamar Thomas injured
his right hip on the first play from scrimmage in Monday night's
17-14 exhibition victory over Green Bay and could be lost for the
season.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas suffered a ''fractured dislocation'' of the hip, team
officials said, after catching a 5-yard pass from Damon Huard. He
was tackled by linebacker Mike Morton and left the field several
minutes later on a stretcher. He was undergoing surgery late Monday
night at Holy Cross Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know the details of the injury,'' Dolphins coach Dave
Wannstedt said. ''As far as his status for the season, we won't
know until tomorrow. ... What a shame. He's had a terrific camp and
a terrific offseason and then this happens.''
</P>
<P>
   In his eight-year career, Thomas has 106 catches for 1,558 yards
and 10 touchdowns. He missed all of last season with a left
shoulder injury sustained during the preseason.
</P>
