<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Jolts Turkey Capital  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) -- A moderate earthquake shook central Turkey
on Tuesday, rattling buildings in the capital. There were no
immediate reports of injuries or damage.
</P>
<P>
   The quake, with a preliminary magnitude of 4.3, struck at 2:40
p.m., Istanbul's Kandilli observatory reported.
</P>
<P>
   The temblor was centered near the town of Beypazari, some 40
miles northwest of Ankara.
</P>
<P>
   The quake occurred five days after the first anniversary of an
earthquake that killed 17,000 in northwestern Turkey. A separate
quake killed about 1,000 people in the region last November.
</P>
<P>
   Much of northern Turkey sits on the active Anatolian fault line.
</P>
</TEXT>
