<HEADLINE> Dow Adds 61; Nasdaq Gains 29  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose Tuesday morning in anxious trading
before a Federal Reserve meeting in which the central bank was
expected to leave interest rates unchanged.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 60.81 at 11,140.62.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also posting modest gains. The
Nasdaq composite index was up 28.74 at 3,981.89, the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 3.13 at 1,502.61, and the Russell 2000
index of smaller companies was up 1.24 at 517.69.
</P>
<P>
   Trading has been light in recent sessions as traders awaited
Tuesday's meeting at the Federal Reserve.
</P>
<P>
   Thanks to a stream of data suggesting the Fed has succeeded in
containing inflation with a 14-month program of interest rate
hikes, analysts believe the central bank won't try to slow the
economy again on Tuesday or any time soon. Fed officials also left
rates unchanged at their meeting last month after boosting them six
times since June 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a slender margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, while Nasdaq gainers held a more
substantial lead.
</P>
<P>
   Volume on the NYSE totaled 102.07 million shares, up from 91.60
million at the same point on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average rose 2.58 percent. In
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was up 0.57 percent,
Britain's FT-SE 100 was up 0.59 percent, and France's CAC-40 was up
0.31 percent.
</P>
