<HEADLINE> Dow Rises 76; Nasdaq Is Up 26  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose Tuesday as investors remained
confident that Federal Reserve officials meeting in Washington will
leave interest rates unchanged again.
</P>
<P>
   At midday on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was
up 75.82 at 11,155.63.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also posting modest gains. The
Nasdaq composite index was up 26.04 at 3,962.65, the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was up 3.45 at 1,502.93, and the Russell 2000
index of smaller companies was up 1.52 at 517.97.
</P>
<P>
   Big movers among the Dow industrials included Honeywell, up
$1.813 at $38.813, and J.P. Morgan, up $3.438 at $148.375. Both
companies would benefit if Fed officials are finished with fighting
inflation by slowing the economy with higher interest rates.
</P>
<P>
   Thanks to a stream of data suggesting the Fed has succeeded in
containing inflation with a 14-month program of rate hikes,
analysts believe the central bank won't try to slow the economy
again on Tuesday or any time soon. Fed officials also left rates
unchanged at their meeting last month after boosting them six times
since June 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a slender margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, while Nasdaq gainers held a more
substantial lead.
</P>
<P>
   Trading was light again as investors awaited the results of
Tuesday's Fed meeting. Volume on the NYSE totaled 350.56 million
shares, up from 330.53 million at the same point on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average rose 2.58 percent.
Germany's DAX index was up 0.55 percent, Britain's FT-SE 100 rose
0.65 percent, and France's CAC-40 was fell 0.88 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ------
