<HEADLINE> Teen charged as adult, arrested for shooting grandfather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LE ROY, N.Y. (AP) - A 15-year-old boy was charged Tuesday as an
adult for the attempted murder of his grandfather.
</P>
<P>
   The grandfather, who requested his name be withheld, was treated
for a gunshot wound Friday night after a bullet went through a
double-paned window of his apartment and lodged just below his
armpit. The 77-year-old man was later released, though the bullet
has not yet been removed.
</P>
<P>
   Devon N. Miller, who lived with his grandparents, was also
charged with stealing the .22-caliber rifle used in the shooting
from the garage of home where he had delivered newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   Police Chief Samuel Steffenilla said Miller was living with his
grandparents up until the arrest early Tuesday morning, and that
they did not suspect the teen in their care.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's bad enough being shot,'' he said. ''But when it's by
someone you love and are trying to help, it's just horrible -
they're devastated.''
</P>
<P>
   Steffinella said the two had a disagreement when Miller was not
allowed to go to a friend's house.
</P>
<P>
   ''The boy wanted to go someplace where the grandfather thought
there would be no adult supervision,'' Steffenilla said.
</P>
<P>
   Steffenilla said Miller left the house after the dispute Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Police found the rifle behind the grandparents' apartment
complex.
</P>
<P>
   Miller was being held in a juvenile detention center until a
hearing Aug. 25. Le Roy is 44 miles east of Buffalo.
</P>
