<HEADLINE> Man charged in stabbing death of estranged wife in McDonald's parking lot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MILLSTONE, N.J. (AP) - A Pennsylvania man was charged with
murder Tuesday in the Monday stabbing death of his estranged wife
in the parking lot of a McDonald's restaurant here, State Police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffrey E. Grant, 43, of Langhorne, Pa., stabbed his wife,
Theresa A. Grant, 40, several times Monday evening in the parking
lot of the restaurant, where she worked, said Sgt. Al Della Fave,
State Police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   When state troopers arrived at the restaurant, they saw Mrs.
Grant, of Seaside Heights, laying on the sidewalk, Della Fave said.
Several bystanders had tried to administer first aid before she was
taken to a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
   At least four witnesses gave statements to police identifying
the killer as Grant's husband, from whom she was separated, Della
Fave said. Mrs. Grant's family members also implicated him, he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Grant was pronounced dead at CentraState Healthcare System
in Freehold, Della Fave said.
</P>
<P>
   Grant was charged Tuesday morning with murder and unlawful
possession of a weapon. He had shaved his mustache and beard in an
attempt to conceal his identity, Della Fave said.
</P>
<P>
   Grant was taken from the Bucks County (Pa.) Jail to be held at
the Monmouth County Correctional Facility in lieu of $1 million
cash bail, Della Fave said.
</P>
</TEXT>
