<HEADLINE> Teen-ager died in apparent fistfight  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WESTFIELD, N.Y. (AP) - Police are awaiting autopsy results
following an Aug. 14 fistfight between 16-year-olds that left one
teen dead.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin M. Callahan died Wednesday in Buffalo's Children's
Hospital from injuries suffered in the fight.
</P>
<P>
   The other combatant, whose name was withheld by police, was
charged with third-degree assault. The youth has since been
released on $1,500 bail. Autopsy results will figure in whether
more serious charges should be filed, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators believe Callahan may have hit his head on the
street or sidewalk during the fight.
</P>
<P>
   The combatants were acquaintances, police said. It still is
unclear what started the fight.
</P>
