<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-22 19:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stuyvesant teacher sues three students for slander  </HEADLINE>
By SAMUEL MAULL
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) - A teacher at Manhattan's Stuyvesant High School
has sued three former students for $6 million each, charging that
they falsely accused him of sexual misconduct because he gave them
low grades.
</P>
<P>
   John Joyce, 32, says in court papers filed late Monday in
Manhattan's State Supreme Court that the allegations caused him to
be removed as a social studies teacher on Sept. 22, 1999, and
assigned to a non-teaching job in the superintendent's office.
</P>
<P>
   The next day, the news media reported that Joyce, a teacher at
the prestigious, highly ranked Stuyvesant for four years, had been
accused of sexual misconduct by two female students.
</P>
<P>
   Court documents say Joyce was ''totally shocked, distraught and
suicidal,'' leading him to seek help from a psychologist. The
papers also say the charges damaged his reputation and career.
</P>
<P>
   The teacher's lawsuit asks $2 million in actual damages and $4
million punitive damages from each of the three students.
</P>
<P>
   Joyce has since returned to his teaching job at Stuyvesant.
Margie Feinberg, a spokeswoman for the Board of Education, said an
investigation found ''no substantial evidence to support the
allegations.''
</P>
<P>
   ''He's tenured and he had the option of transferring, but he
elected to stay at (Stuyvesant),'' Feinberg said. She said a letter
of admonition was put in his file and he was cautioned.
</P>
<P>
   Joyce's papers quote one girl as saying she was ''tired of
having that pervert looking down my blouse.'' She also said she saw
Joyce reach to touch a girl's arm, ''pretend to slip,'' and touch
the girl's breast.
</P>
<P>
   The same girl also said Joyce ''is not a very good teacher and
often makes inappropriate comments such as, 'How is the Holocaust
like a big barbecue?' and 'Everybody knows that there are Jews and
Blacks in the KKK,''' Joyce's court papers say.
</P>
<P>
   The documents say the girl's accusations are false. The student
was angry that he ''gave her a final grade of 85 in European
History and was assigned to him again for American History,'' court
papers say.
</P>
<P>
   A second female student alleged that Joyce ''hovered around her
or stood near her and asked how she was doing,'' court papers say.
She is quoted as saying she ''frequently felt like crying after
leaving his class.''
</P>
<P>
   Joyce's papers say she had ''received a failing grade (55) in
the Spring term.'' They say she ''plagiarized, with two students,
three homework assignments and cheated on her term essay with the
same students.''
</P>
<P>
   A male student supported the female students' accusations. Court
papers quote him saying Joyce ''has a habit of staring at the
female students.''
</P>
<P>
   But the male student ''was also unhappy with his final grade
from the previous year'' and was not pleased that Joyce kept him
from dominating every class discussion, Joyce's papers say.
</P>
<P>
   Neither the students nor their parents could be found for
comment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
