<HEADLINE> Girl dies during sailing program at Old Greenwich Yacht Club  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) - A 9-year-old girl died Tuesday while
participating in a sailing program with the Old Greenwich Yacht
Club in Long Island Sound.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they are not sure if the girl drown, or if something
else led to her death.
</P>
<P>
   She was in the water just before noon, practicing uprighting a
14-foot sailboat, when a member of the yacht club staff noticed she
was not moving, police said. Yacht club staff immediately began
lifesaving efforts, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The girl was taken to a nearby dock at the south end of
Greenwich Point where paramedics tried to revive her. She was
transported to Stamford Hospital and pronounced dead just after 3
p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Her name was not released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Police said they were treating the death as a boating accident,
pending the outcome of an autopsy.
</P>
<P>
   The girl was one of 13 children, all between 9-and-11-years old,
participating in the junior sailing program operated by the
Longshore Sailing School at the yacht club. The children were under
the supervision of certified instructors, police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
