<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baseball Grand Slam Record Set  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI (AP) -- Alex Ochoa hit the 142nd grand slam of the
season Tuesday night, setting a major league record.
</P>
<P>
   The Cincinnati Reds outfielder hit his first career slam in the
first inning against Philadelphia's Bruce Chen, the Reds' second
slam in two nights. Dmitri Young hit an upper-deck grand slam in a
7-4 win Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Reds, who lost 5-4, hadn't hit grand slams in consecutive
games since May 4-5, 1996, when Eric Davis had a pair. They have
five overall this season.
</P>
<P>
   The record was tied earlier Tuesday in San Diego when the
Padres' Damian Jackson hit No. 141.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson connected in the second inning off Pat Mahomes for his
first career slam, San Diego's fourth of the season, in a 16-1 win
over the New York Mets.
</P>
<P>
   The previous record of 141 slams was set in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
